      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The market:</strong> Auburn-Lewiston is Maine's second metro area. Auburn specifically serves its own residents — convenience matters more than curation.</li>
        <li><strong>Best location:</strong> Mount Auburn Avenue corridor near the mall. Lower rent, errand-run foot traffic, underserved by existing dispensaries.</li>
        <li><strong>Customer profile:</strong> Working families, mid-40s median age. Price-conscious but not bargain hunters. Flower and edibles dominate. Medical crossover is significant.</li>
        <li><strong>Competitive reality:</strong> 3-4 existing stores, not all of them are good. Your edge is convenience and consistency, not product differentiation.</li>
        <li><strong>Startup:</strong> $300K-$400K all-in. Don't under-budget — Auburn's margin for error is narrower than Portland's.</li>
      </ul>
